WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:02.966
We always say anti-aging, anti-aging.

00:00:02.966 --> 00:00:04.600
but have you ever thought that 

00:00:04.600 --> 00:00:08.500
“Aging” and “Senescence” may be different concepts.

00:00:08.733 --> 00:00:10.800
Aging refers to the imprint of time.

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:12.000
It is the natural progression of age.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:12.933
It is an objective rule.

00:00:12.933 --> 00:00:14.866
It is something that none of us can escape.

00:00:14.866 --> 00:00:17.333
senescence, on the other hand, refers to the loss of vitality

00:00:17.333 --> 00:00:19.433
It involves Functional disorder and degeneration.

00:00:19.433 --> 00:00:20.500
It can occur at

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:22.733
any stage of our lives

00:00:22.733 --> 00:00:25.600
and is not necessarily related to time or age.

00:00:25.666 --> 00:00:27.300
If we compare our lives

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:29.066
to a river,

00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:33.000
Aging is like the river flowing continuously forward,

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.033
while senescence is like the river

00:00:36.033 --> 00:00:37.300
initially having plenty of

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:39.700
water , then gradually slowing down, decreasing,

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:41.200
and eventually drying up.

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:43.900
Aging, to some extent, is irreversible,

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:46.066
just as our river flows continuously forward,

00:00:46.066 --> 00:00:47.800
and time is unidirectional.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.433
However, senescence can be mitigated through regular exercise,

00:00:50.433 --> 00:00:51.433
a healthy diet,

00:00:51.433 --> 00:00:54.266
or proper care. Since we can regulate it,

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:57.100
what we usually call anti-aging

00:00:57.133 --> 00:00:59.833
should more accurately be called anti-senescence.

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:02.233
That is, we use various methods

00:01:02.233 --> 00:01:04.900
and good skincare to regulate it,

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:05.933
so that our skin

00:01:05.933 --> 00:01:08.300
can stay in a good state

00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:09.700
for a longer period of time,

00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:13.066
and and the water in our 'river channel' can remain as abundant as possible, 

00:01:13.066 --> 00:01:14.933
so that we will look young.

00:01:15.233 --> 00:01:17.000
Hi everyone, I’m Formulator Xingxing.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:21.233
Today I’m going to talk about the “3+1 Anti-senescence（Aging） Method”.

00:01:28.266 --> 00:01:30.266
Before we officially talk about Anti-senescence methods,

00:01:30.266 --> 00:01:32.133
let's think about a question,

00:01:32.133 --> 00:01:35.633
What are the characteristics of youthful skin

00:01:35.633 --> 00:01:37.300
versus aging skin?

00:01:37.433 --> 00:01:38.500
Youthful skin

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:39.300
has elasticity,

00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:40.666
glows with no wrinkles,

00:01:40.666 --> 00:01:42.433
no dark spots, with great complexion.

00:01:42.433 --> 00:01:43.533
Aging skin, however,

00:01:43.533 --> 00:01:44.533
shows poor complexion,

00:01:44.533 --> 00:01:45.500
looks dull and yellowish,

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:46.133
and has liver spots,

00:01:46.133 --> 00:01:47.000
melasma appears,

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:47.700
wrinkles show up,

00:01:47.700 --> 00:01:49.000
skin sags and becomes deflated.

00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:50.833
So how does a person age?

00:01:50.833 --> 00:01:53.466
How does the water in the river disappear?

00:01:53.466 --> 00:01:55.400
We divide this process

00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:57.300
into three stages

00:02:00.066 --> 00:02:03.266
These three stages are the Radiance Decline Stage,

00:02:03.333 --> 00:02:06.466
the Wrinkle Formation Stage, and the Sagging &amp; Deflation Stage.

00:02:06.633 --> 00:02:09.200
Stage One — Radiance Decline Stage,

00:02:09.200 --> 00:02:12.300
refers to changes in skin radiance,

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:15.266
skin tone, and complexion.

00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:18.733
Typical signs are tired-looking skin,

00:02:18.733 --> 00:02:20.033
yellowish and dull,

00:02:20.033 --> 00:02:21.033
darkened skin,

00:02:21.033 --> 00:02:23.233
even loss of glow and elasticity.

00:02:23.233 --> 00:02:24.733
Spots also begin to appear on the face.

00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:27.400
Stage Two — Wrinkle Formation Stage.

00:02:27.433 --> 00:02:28.500
At this stage,

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:29.666
we first notice

00:02:29.666 --> 00:02:32.400
wrinkles appear when making facial expressions—

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:33.533
such as crow's feet and

00:02:33.533 --> 00:02:34.333
expression lines

00:02:34.333 --> 00:02:37.266
Gradually, even without expressions,

00:02:37.266 --> 00:02:38.666
wrinkles also appear on the face

00:02:38.666 --> 00:02:40.533
like nasolabial folds,

00:02:40.533 --> 00:02:41.333
marionette lines, and

00:02:41.333 --> 00:02:43.800
tear troughs — these are static wrinkles (true wrinkles).

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:46.900
Stage Three — Sagging &amp; Deflation Stage.

00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:49.866
As wrinkles deepen,

00:02:49.866 --> 00:02:52.033
the elasticity and support of the skin

00:02:52.033 --> 00:02:53.633
further decreases.

00:02:53.633 --> 00:02:56.033
Then you see your face

00:02:56.033 --> 00:02:57.200
is no longer holding up.

00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:58.633
It sags and the jawline expands,

00:02:58.633 --> 00:02:59.633
eventually collapsing downward.

00:02:59.733 --> 00:03:01.933
Of course, because everyone's skin type

00:03:01.933 --> 00:03:03.633
and environment are different

00:03:03.633 --> 00:03:04.133
therefore,

00:03:04.133 --> 00:03:07.233
the timing of these stages may vary

00:03:07.233 --> 00:03:08.500
from person to person.

00:03:08.533 --> 00:03:11.033
But the overall progression is similar.

00:03:11.033 --> 00:03:12.666
It follows this sequence

00:03:12.800 --> 00:03:16.200
as we mentioned earlier, aging is an objective law that

00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:17.700
we cannot resist.

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:19.800
Once your Aging progresses

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.033
into the next stage,

00:03:22.033 --> 00:03:25.300
it is very difficult to reverse it to the previous stage.

00:03:25.433 --> 00:03:26.033
Therefore,

00:03:26.033 --> 00:03:30.133
we need to use proper skincare methods to combat senescence,

00:03:30.133 --> 00:03:31.500
and keep your skin

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:34.933
stay in the current stage as long as possible.

00:03:34.933 --> 00:03:36.933
long as possible. To give

00:03:37.133 --> 00:03:39.333
an example, if we don't take care of our skin,

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:41.800
our radiance might fade by age 25 and

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:43.700
our face might sag by age 35.

00:03:43.833 --> 00:03:45.800
But if we take good care of ourselves,

00:03:45.800 --> 00:03:48.266
our radiance might only start to fade at age 30,

00:03:48.266 --> 00:03:50.633
and our face might not sag by age 55.

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:53.566
Wouldn't we look younger than our peers?

00:03:53.566 --> 00:03:55.000
After listening to my

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:57.066
description of the phenomena in these three stages,

00:03:57.066 --> 00:03:59.066
it's easy to see

00:03:59.066 --> 00:04:00.466
which stage

00:04:00.466 --> 00:04:02.633
you're currently in.

00:04:02.800 --> 00:04:03.933
If you're still young

00:04:03.933 --> 00:04:06.066
and haven't entered these three stages yet , then we

00:04:06.066 --> 00:04:07.866
should try our best to avoid stepping into them

00:04:07.866 --> 00:04:10.300
through proper skincare.

00:04:10.633 --> 00:04:12.333
But if you're already

00:04:12.333 --> 00:04:14.266
in one of these three stages,

00:04:14.266 --> 00:04:16.266
then our anti-senescence goal

00:04:16.266 --> 00:04:19.000
is to stop time in that stage.

00:04:22.233 --> 00:04:24.100
Hearing this, you're probably eager

00:04:24.100 --> 00:04:25.900
to learn the methods that follow,

00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:27.700
but before we get to the main topic... Before

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:30.700
we need to understand one crucial concept.

00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:34.600
They are Functional disorder and Organic change.

00:04:34.666 --> 00:04:36.533
So what is Functional disorder?

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:37.400
For example,

00:04:37.400 --> 00:04:38.866
if you have diarrhea

00:04:38.866 --> 00:04:40.133
or a headache,

00:04:40.233 --> 00:04:41.733
and you go to the hospital

00:04:41.733 --> 00:04:42.900
for a colonoscopy

00:04:42.900 --> 00:04:43.500
or an endoscopy,

00:04:43.500 --> 00:04:45.833
or a brain CT scan,

00:04:45.900 --> 00:04:48.000
the results

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:49.266
might be completely normal.

00:04:49.266 --> 00:04:50.300
You still experience

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:51.633
But you do have diarrhea.

00:04:51.633 --> 00:04:52.700
Your head really hurts.

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:53.600
This means that

00:04:53.600 --> 00:04:56.866
your organs themselves haven't changed,

00:04:56.866 --> 00:04:59.633
heir functions have been impaired,

00:04:59.633 --> 00:05:00.800
It malfunctions,

00:05:00.833 --> 00:05:02.400
leading to illness.

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:03.533
You feel uncomfortable.

00:05:03.666 --> 00:05:05.800
So then what is Organic change?

00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:08.200
For example, not only stomach discomfort,

00:05:08.200 --> 00:05:09.800
also a stomach ulcer

00:05:09.800 --> 00:05:11.800
Or due to high blood lipids,

00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:13.100
you have a cerebral infarction.

00:05:13.100 --> 00:05:14.500
However, after visiting the hospital,

00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:18.000
changes can be detected through gastroscopy or head CT scans

00:05:18.033 --> 00:05:19.333
scans, as they can detect changes

00:05:19.333 --> 00:05:22.333
in these organs.

00:05:22.333 --> 00:05:23.033
In other words,

00:05:23.033 --> 00:05:25.266
when we observe structural changes in organs

00:05:25.266 --> 00:05:27.700
through imaging,

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:29.433
this is referred to as organic change.

00:05:29.433 --> 00:05:31.633
The aging process of the body

00:05:31.633 --> 00:05:34.866
is essentially

00:05:34.866 --> 00:05:38.033
an evolution from functional impairment to structural change.

00:05:38.033 --> 00:05:40.800
As the largest organ in the body, the skin

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:42.800
also follows this pattern.

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:44.800
Now let's review

00:05:44.800 --> 00:05:46.933
the three stages of skin aging.

00:05:47.033 --> 00:05:49.333
The first stage is the loss of radiance.

00:05:49.400 --> 00:05:50.400
During this stage,

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:51.433
the overall metabolic rate of

00:05:51.433 --> 00:05:54.133
our skin begins to slow down,

00:05:54.133 --> 00:05:56.700
and a large number of free radicals

00:05:56.700 --> 00:05:57.933
or free sugars

00:05:58.000 --> 00:05:59.500
accumulate in the skin . These substances

00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:01.666
adhere to the collagen,

00:06:01.666 --> 00:06:02.633
causing it

00:06:02.833 --> 00:06:05.100
to denature. As a result, your skin will darken,

00:06:05.100 --> 00:06:06.633
and lose its structural support. This decreases

00:06:06.633 --> 00:06:09.300
sskin elasticity and radiance, leading to duller skin.

00:06:09.300 --> 00:06:10.300
In simple terms,

00:06:10.300 --> 00:06:12.300
the skin

00:06:12.300 --> 00:06:14.566
has developed typical functional impairments

00:06:14.566 --> 00:06:16.933
due to external aggressors.

00:06:17.066 --> 00:06:20.200
Our main focus in skincare during this period

00:06:20.333 --> 00:06:22.666
is to address

00:06:22.666 --> 00:06:26.233
the factors contributing to these impairments. For instance, if

00:06:26.266 --> 00:06:27.933
the skin is damaged

00:06:27.933 --> 00:06:29.600
due to an excess of free radicals,

00:06:29.600 --> 00:06:32.000
we eliminate those free radicals.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:34.000
If the skin’s function

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:35.466
is caused by an excess of free sugars,

00:06:35.466 --> 00:06:37.800
we fight glycation,

00:06:37.800 --> 00:06:39.500
by reducing free sugars and

00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:41.000
advanced glycation end-products.

00:06:41.033 --> 00:06:44.066
In skincare terms,

00:06:44.066 --> 00:06:46.900
we focus on four things:

00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:49.000
anti-oxidation, anti-glycation, 

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:51.133
anti-carbonylation, and anti-blue light.

00:06:51.133 --> 00:06:54.433
These are the four main approaches to maintaining skin function.

00:06:54.500 --> 00:06:56.633
And what about the ingredients that support these functions?

00:06:56.633 --> 00:06:59.233
There are many, such as the Vitamin C family

00:06:59.233 --> 00:07:02.433
(Vitamin C (Ascorbic Acid), VCIP, 3-O-Ethyl Ascorbic Acid (Ethyl Ascorbic Acid), etc.), 

00:07:02.433 --> 00:07:04.533
or the polyphenol family

00:07:04.533 --> 00:07:05.733
Tea Polyphenols

00:07:05.733 --> 00:07:07.133
anthocyanins, oleuropein,

00:07:07.133 --> 00:07:08.033
hydroxytyrosol, 

00:07:08.033 --> 00:07:09.900
and the carotenoid family

00:07:09.900 --> 00:07:10.933
lycopene,

00:07:10.933 --> 00:07:11.666
astaxanthin, 

00:07:11.666 --> 00:07:14.666
as well as various antioxidant and anti-carbonylation ingredients

00:07:14.700 --> 00:07:16.033
such as Tocopherol,

00:07:16.033 --> 00:07:16.700
ergothioneine,

00:07:16.700 --> 00:07:19.633
idebenone, and Ubiquinone. SOD

00:07:19.700 --> 00:07:22.066
and other good ingredients for anti-glycation and anti-blue light,

00:07:22.066 --> 00:07:23.600
such as carnosine and Anserine.

00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:25.633
I've listed so many ingredients at once, 

00:07:25.633 --> 00:07:26.866
you might feel dizzy, 

00:07:26.866 --> 00:07:30.266
but their functions don't overlap. Instead, 

00:07:30.266 --> 00:07:32.000
they each have their own areas of expertise.

00:07:32.133 --> 00:07:34.000
For example, ingredients like 3-O-Ethyl Ascorbic Acid (Ethyl Ascorbic Acid)

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:36.466
and Oleuropein、 Hydroxytyrosol 

00:07:36.466 --> 00:07:39.533
they are more suitable for oily skin of anti-oxidation, 

00:07:39.533 --> 00:07:40.700
while ingredients like Tocopherol, 

00:07:40.700 --> 00:07:43.200
astaxanthin, and VCIP

00:07:43.200 --> 00:07:45.700
are more suitable for dry skin in terms of anti-oxidation.

00:07:45.766 --> 00:07:48.000
There are also some special ingredients, 

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:49.333
such as idebenone

00:07:49.333 --> 00:07:50.600
and Ubiquinone, 

00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:52.333
which have strong effects

00:07:52.333 --> 00:07:53.600
but they can be irritating

00:07:53.600 --> 00:07:54.700
and not suitable for sensitive skin.

00:07:54.833 --> 00:07:55.700
On the contrary,

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:57.200
ingredients like baicalin and rutin

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:59.500
are practically designed for sensitive skin.

00:07:59.666 --> 00:08:01.066
Okay, now we've finished

00:08:01.066 --> 00:08:02.033
the first stage,

00:08:02.033 --> 00:08:04.933
which focuses on four key anti-aging strategies:

00:08:04.933 --> 00:08:06.233
anti-oxidation, 

00:08:06.233 --> 00:08:07.266
anti-carbonylation,

00:08:07.266 --> 00:08:09.000
anti-glycation, and anti-blue light.

00:08:09.500 --> 00:08:11.900
The second stage is the wrinkle appearance stage.

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:12.666
At this stage,

00:08:12.666 --> 00:08:14.000
we first need to distinguish

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:16.400
what type of wrinkles you have on your face.

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:17.300
One type is wrinkles

00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:19.000
that appear when you make facial expressions, 

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:20.033
such as laughing or

00:08:20.033 --> 00:08:20.733
crying, etc.

00:08:20.733 --> 00:08:22.466
only then wrinkles show up.

00:08:22.500 --> 00:08:24.000
But when you are expressionless,

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:25.533
you don’t see noticeable wrinkles.

00:08:25.666 --> 00:08:28.133
This type is called Pseudo wrinkles,

00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:29.400
also known as expression lines.

00:08:29.533 --> 00:08:30.533
The second type

00:08:30.533 --> 00:08:33.233
remains on your face even without expressions,

00:08:33.233 --> 00:08:34.900
still visible.

00:08:34.933 --> 00:08:36.200
Like your forehead lines,

00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:37.333
nasolabial folds,

00:08:37.333 --> 00:08:39.300
marionette lines, tear troughs, etc.

00:08:39.466 --> 00:08:42.100
These are called True wrinkles.

00:08:42.266 --> 00:08:43.533
In summary,

00:08:43.533 --> 00:08:47.900
when your wrinkles are mainly expression lines,

00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:49.266
your skin

00:08:49.266 --> 00:08:52.666
your skin is primarily in a state of functional decline.

00:08:52.733 --> 00:08:54.600
However, when your wrinkles are mainly

00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:56.466
true wrinkles,

00:08:56.466 --> 00:08:58.033
you've entered

00:08:58.033 --> 00:09:00.000
a stage of organic change.

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:01.100
This change

00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:02.033
leads to

00:09:02.033 --> 00:09:03.300
completely different ingredients

00:09:03.300 --> 00:09:05.533
and skincare methods.

00:09:05.733 --> 00:09:07.433
In the expression line stage,

00:09:07.433 --> 00:09:08.733
our skincare theme

00:09:08.733 --> 00:09:11.700
should continue the four-pronged approach from the previous stage,

00:09:11.766 --> 00:09:12.700
while also

00:09:12.700 --> 00:09:13.733
incorporating

00:09:13.733 --> 00:09:16.800
a type of ingredient unique to this stagee —

00:09:16.800 --> 00:09:19.233
Neuro-signaling peptides.

00:09:19.400 --> 00:09:20.666
Since pseudo-wrinkles,

00:09:20.666 --> 00:09:22.066
also known as  expression lines,

00:09:22.100 --> 00:09:22.866
they are caused by 

00:09:22.866 --> 00:09:26.066
excessive facial expressions and

00:09:26.066 --> 00:09:28.500
muscle contraction.

00:09:28.633 --> 00:09:30.666
Neurotransmitter peptides

00:09:30.666 --> 00:09:32.300
can inhibit

00:09:32.300 --> 00:09:33.733
or slow down

00:09:33.733 --> 00:09:37.100
the frequency and intensity of these skin contractions.

00:09:37.300 --> 00:09:39.300
When the contractions become less

00:09:39.300 --> 00:09:40.666
frequent,

00:09:40.666 --> 00:09:42.200
your wrinkles fade

00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:43.233
and lessen.

00:09:43.300 --> 00:09:45.000
Common ingredients of this type

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:46.200
include botulinum toxin,

00:09:46.200 --> 00:09:47.866
snake venom peptides, and Idealifting.

00:09:47.866 --> 00:09:49.066
Spiropeptides and similar

00:09:49.066 --> 00:09:49.700
ingredients

00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:52.800
work by mimicking the effects of Botox

00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:54.266
to reduce skin contraction

00:09:54.266 --> 00:09:55.600
and thus reduce wrinkles.

00:09:55.633 --> 00:09:58.666
However, once true wrinkles appear,

00:09:58.666 --> 00:10:01.900
superficial methods like reducing facial contraction

00:10:01.900 --> 00:10:03.100
become ineffective.

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:05.233
At this point, we need to focus on

00:10:05.233 --> 00:10:07.933
increasing collagen in the dermis of the skin,

00:10:07.933 --> 00:10:08.633
elastin,

00:10:08.633 --> 00:10:10.466
and fibronectin in the dermis

00:10:10.533 --> 00:10:12.133
improving its structural support

00:10:12.133 --> 00:10:14.666
and helping it regain firmness.

00:10:14.733 --> 00:10:17.400
A typical ingredient

00:10:17.400 --> 00:10:18.900
well-suited for this

00:10:18.900 --> 00:10:20.533
the Retinol (Vitamin A) family,

00:10:20.533 --> 00:10:21.733
Its derivatives include

00:10:21.733 --> 00:10:23.433
plant-derived retinoids.

00:10:23.433 --> 00:10:26.333
Both families are suitable.

00:10:26.666 --> 00:10:27.866
It's important to note that

00:10:27.866 --> 00:10:29.900
becauseVitamin A has a property —

00:10:29.900 --> 00:10:32.500
while thickening the dermis,

00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:34.300
it thins the stratum corneum.

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:34.833
So,

00:10:34.833 --> 00:10:38.066
for East Asians who naturally have a thinner stratum corneum,

00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:39.700
the irritation risk of Vitamin A

00:10:39.700 --> 00:10:40.466
is relatively high.

00:10:40.466 --> 00:10:42.900
So at this stage, when applying ingredients,

00:10:42.900 --> 00:10:44.233
there is one principle:

00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:46.633
“Step by step.”

00:10:46.666 --> 00:10:49.666
We start with gentler plant-derived retinoids

00:10:49.666 --> 00:10:50.666
or retinyl esters,

00:10:50.666 --> 00:10:52.600
then gradually transition to retinol,

00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:54.533
and then further to retinaldehyde (Retinal).

00:10:54.600 --> 00:10:55.133
Moreover,

00:10:55.133 --> 00:10:58.133
the concentration must also increase gradually.

00:10:58.133 --> 00:11:00.200
Start low, then go higher.

00:11:00.300 --> 00:11:03.133
Do not take chances here.

00:11:03.200 --> 00:11:06.466
If your skin crashes and becomes irritated,

00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:08.300
your skin will age faster.

00:11:08.666 --> 00:11:10.800
As wrinkles deepen 

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:12.733
and skin support continues to weaken,

00:11:12.733 --> 00:11:14.433
we enter 3rd Stage —

00:11:14.433 --> 00:11:16.600
Sagging &amp; Deflation Stage.

00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:17.500
This stage

00:11:17.500 --> 00:11:19.233
visually,

00:11:19.233 --> 00:11:20.833
the face changes dramatically,

00:11:20.833 --> 00:11:24.433
so it’s often called a “cliff-like aging stage.”

00:11:24.433 --> 00:11:27.033
Whether your skin is sagging,

00:11:27.033 --> 00:11:29.033
deflated, or drooping,

00:11:29.033 --> 00:11:31.700
it all comes down to **Organic change**.

00:11:31.833 --> 00:11:34.133
On a microscopic level,

00:11:34.133 --> 00:11:35.000
at this stage,

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:37.033
what happens to our skin?

00:11:37.066 --> 00:11:39.466
Massive collagen loss,

00:11:39.466 --> 00:11:42.033
elastic fiber bundles snapping apart,

00:11:42.033 --> 00:11:44.400
the basement membrane’s adhesion weakens,

00:11:44.400 --> 00:11:46.933
epidermis and dermis stop communicating,

00:11:46.933 --> 00:11:49.733
no metabolic exchange between them.

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:52.600
The whole skin loses its moisturizing ability,

00:11:52.600 --> 00:11:54.900
and stability drops significantly.

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:56.933
Some may think:

00:11:56.933 --> 00:11:58.066
“I’m already so old,

00:11:58.066 --> 00:11:59.800
shouldn’t I use something strong

00:11:59.800 --> 00:12:01.666
to bring my skin back to life?”

00:12:01.666 --> 00:12:04.033
I’m telling you — absolutely not.

00:12:04.066 --> 00:12:07.133
Because your skin barrier system

00:12:07.133 --> 00:12:10.700
is undergoing a full-scale collapse.

00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:11.300
At this moment,

00:12:11.300 --> 00:12:12.533
your barrier system

00:12:12.533 --> 00:12:14.233
barely functions.

00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:15.600
If you add strong actives,

00:12:15.633 --> 00:12:17.800
there’s only one outcome —

00:12:17.800 --> 00:12:18.666
allergic reaction.

00:12:18.733 --> 00:12:21.066
And if you get irritated now,

00:12:21.066 --> 00:12:23.000
it will further

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:25.100
speed up your aging process,

00:12:25.100 --> 00:12:27.933
making your face more saggy, dry, and deflated.

00:12:28.233 --> 00:12:32.033
So the main task of skincare at this moment

00:12:32.033 --> 00:12:34.433
is not to use strong products

00:12:34.433 --> 00:12:35.733
to reverse time,

00:12:35.733 --> 00:12:37.600
but to do our best

00:12:37.600 --> 00:12:39.600
to help the skin maintain

00:12:39.600 --> 00:12:40.900
good moisturized,

00:12:40.900 --> 00:12:43.000
and comfortable state .

00:12:43.066 --> 00:12:43.900
Because the skin

00:12:43.900 --> 00:12:45.500
will become increasingly dry

00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:47.700
so in product selection,

00:12:47.700 --> 00:12:49.433
we must focus on

00:12:49.433 --> 00:12:52.866
products and ingredients with higher lipid content,

00:12:53.066 --> 00:12:55.100
Only in this way can it seal in moisture

00:12:55.100 --> 00:12:56.133
and reduce water loss,

00:12:56.133 --> 00:12:58.133
maintaining barrier integrity.

00:12:58.266 --> 00:12:59.733
At the same time, we can also use

00:12:59.733 --> 00:13:02.866
ingredients that help the skin produce fillers.

00:13:02.900 --> 00:13:03.933
Typical ingredients

00:13:03.933 --> 00:13:06.300
include Pro-Xylane,

00:13:06.300 --> 00:13:08.800
Sodium Hyaluronate Crosspolymer, Acetylated Hyaluronic Acid,

00:13:08.800 --> 00:13:09.633
Collagen

00:13:09.633 --> 00:13:10.433
Fibronectin

00:13:10.433 --> 00:13:11.400
Elastin / Hydrolyzed Elastin.

00:13:11.433 --> 00:13:12.000
And then there

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:14.533
are oil-based ingredients

00:13:14.533 --> 00:13:15.600
that can replenish the sebum film and interstitial fluid,

00:13:15.600 --> 00:13:16.333
such as squalane and

00:13:16.333 --> 00:13:18.033
Limnanthes Alba Seed Oil.

00:13:18.033 --> 00:13:19.900
When the skin is fully moisturized,

00:13:19.900 --> 00:13:21.400
softened, and plumped,

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:23.633
we can make our face

00:13:23.633 --> 00:13:25.033
look softer, 

00:13:25.033 --> 00:13:26.533
more hydrated, more radiant, 

00:13:26.533 --> 00:13:27.266
and fuller than before. 

00:13:27.266 --> 00:13:28.333
Speaking of which,

00:13:28.333 --> 00:13:29.533
some people will definitely ask,

00:13:29.533 --> 00:13:31.933
do the ingredients and products for these three stages

00:13:31.933 --> 00:13:33.633
overlap?

00:13:33.733 --> 00:13:36.133
Well, they don't really overlap much.

00:13:36.233 --> 00:13:39.000
So you must

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:40.533
use the right product for the right stage.

00:13:40.533 --> 00:13:41.733
 If you use the wrong one, 

00:13:41.733 --> 00:13:44.600
you may end up looking

00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:45.800
older even after fighting aging for so long.

00:13:46.133 --> 00:13:47.433
Another question is, 

00:13:47.433 --> 00:13:49.466
What exactly can skincare

00:13:49.466 --> 00:13:51.666
achieve?

00:13:51.666 --> 00:13:53.466
If my methods are correct,

00:13:53.466 --> 00:13:54.600
and taken in time,

00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:57.333
can this stage be reversed?

00:13:57.366 --> 00:13:58.600
Here’s the answer:

00:13:58.600 --> 00:14:02.100
if you are still in the **Functional Disorder** stage,

00:14:02.100 --> 00:14:02.733
that means —

00:14:02.733 --> 00:14:05.433
the dullness phase or expression-line phase,

00:14:05.466 --> 00:14:06.666
then timely skincare

00:14:06.666 --> 00:14:08.200
with correct methods

00:14:08.333 --> 00:14:11.433
has a chance of restoring it to some extent.

00:14:11.533 --> 00:14:14.666
But if you’ve entered the **Organic Change** stage,

00:14:14.666 --> 00:14:16.066
such as true wrinkles,

00:14:16.066 --> 00:14:17.000
and sagging face,

00:14:17.033 --> 00:14:20.200
the longer you stay in organic change,

00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.300
the slower the recovery becomes,

00:14:22.300 --> 00:14:23.733
the longer it take,

00:14:23.733 --> 00:14:27.266
and simple skincare can hardly reverse it.

00:14:27.400 --> 00:14:30.200
Therefore, our anti-aging not only requires the right methods but

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:31.600
also timely intervention.

00:14:32.266 --> 00:14:35.866
Next, let’s talk about anti-aging for each stage

00:14:35.866 --> 00:14:37.300
and the products they correspond to.

00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:45.233
Before choosing products, we should pay attention to the following

00:14:45.233 --> 00:14:47.300
When we choose the products

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:49.733
for our current stage,

00:14:49.866 --> 00:14:52.133
we must also keep

00:14:52.133 --> 00:14:54.733
a product from the previous stage.

00:14:54.833 --> 00:14:56.866
For example, if I am in the wrinkle stage

00:14:56.866 --> 00:14:58.466
and I am using retinol,

00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:00.700
I should also combine

00:15:00.700 --> 00:15:02.400
