00:22:46.600 --> 00:22:48.800
Another ingredient suitable for this stage

00:22:48.800 --> 00:22:51.266
is the increasingly popular PDRN.

00:22:51.300 --> 00:22:54.066
PDRN comes from salmon DNA fragments,

00:22:54.066 --> 00:22:57.733
and these salmon DNA fragments

00:22:57.733 --> 00:23:00.266
share about 95% similarity with human DNA.

00:23:00.300 --> 00:23:03.433
So when your skin absorbs these DNA fragments,

00:23:03.466 --> 00:23:05.100
they can be utilized by our cells

00:23:05.100 --> 00:23:06.233
to activate cell activity,

00:23:06.233 --> 00:23:07.233
self-repair

00:23:07.233 --> 00:23:10.033
and stimulate collagen-producing pathways.

00:23:10.033 --> 00:23:11.200
Previously,

00:23:11.200 --> 00:23:14.666
PDRN was mainly used in injectable mesotherapy,

00:23:14.666 --> 00:23:17.333
or ultra-luxury skincare brands like Valmont,

00:23:17.333 --> 00:23:20.000
in very high-end product lines.

00:23:20.066 --> 00:23:20.700
But now,

00:23:20.700 --> 00:23:22.700
with technological advancement,

00:23:22.700 --> 00:23:25.700
the challenge of PDRN skin absorption

00:23:25.700 --> 00:23:27.800
has gradually been improved.

00:23:27.866 --> 00:23:29.466
So we’ve been seeing more launches of

00:23:29.466 --> 00:23:32.466
various topical PDRN products.

